#YindulgeAndRestore 
Day 4 #sphinx 
Let's open our hearts to Day 4! This pose is such a sweet way to tone the spine - we have the support of the floor to allow us to ground or uplift however much we need. *Just be sure you don't feel any sharp pain in the low back*
From hands and knees, lower your forearms. Walk your knees back until it feels ok to release the hips to the floor (can place a blanket under the hips for padding). Widen the feet at least to hip-width, if not wider, deepening on what feels best on your low back. Stack the elbows under the shoulders. Let your head rest (maybe on a block). Enjoy for 3-5 minutes. 
Affirmation: I feel pleasure and abundance with every breath.

Burning has long been used as a ritual for cleansing and releasing situations and relationships that have caused you pain. You can burn alone, or you can burn with friends or loved ones, most people like to do “bonfires.” You sit in front of your pot or burning space, hold the images/paper in your hands and just speak from the heart about what this represents to you and why you need to let this go. Then finish with the words “I release you. I am done.” Whether it was a part of the script or not I appreciate them including it in the episode. It was a rare moment when they ladies actually bonded and shared what they were truly feeling.💙💜 #LetsTalk What is your method of release?
